race.description: Become A Brc Member Maiden Plate
race.comment: Looks a nice progression for SEVILO (3) out to the mile. Well in the market on debut and would up strongly over seven furlongs, finishing third but less than two lengths form the winner Heavenly Conquest. Blinkers added and has big upside. Hard to beat. FLOP SHOT (1) was fair on debut then ran a much improved race in the same race as SEVILO, winding up late four fourth. Looks well suited by the extra ground and is a definite threat. DIVERSITY (6) was beaten for speed on debut but did much better over seven furlongs last time, also in the Heavenly Conquest race. Looks as though is crying out for the ground so don't underestimate. SHE CAN SOAR (7) has been thereabouts, the latest getting going late over 1830m at Eagle Farm. Has a bit of experience over the trip on the others and expected to be grinding home again. TEDDY TOO CHEAP (4) was safely held on debut over 1200m but has good upside over the extra ground.
